ymmetric interactions in cellular systems -- or general\nactive systems -- control cluster sizes and polarity, and can prevent large\nscale coarsening and long range polarity, except in the singular regime of\ndense confluent systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Dec 2020 19:26:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-03"}
