of the cosine-profile of A (B) around\nthe minima of solar cycles is about 41% (65%) larger than that of A (B) around\nthe maxima. In addition, the cosine profiles of A and B suggest a large (up to\n180 degree) phase difference between the long-term variations of A, and also\nbetween those of B, around maxima and minima of solar cycles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Dec 2020 13:28:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-04"}
